- What are you doing?
- Stay there! Don't move!

170
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,802
- Identify yourself!
- Get back here right now!

171
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,680
Whoever it is,
they couldn't have made it very far.

172
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:54,365
I'll alert CDC to keep an eye out.

173
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:55,607
They're en route.

174
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:58,650
- There's no way this attack was human.
- You don't know that.

175
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:01,290
Don't know what?

176
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,170
The guy's shredded.
His throat was...

177
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:05,243
-...in the gutter.
- Just let me handle it.

178
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:07,801
What's to handle?
This has Lycan written all over it.

179
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:08,609
Detective...

180
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:12,128
...when was the last time you heard
about a reported Lycan killing?

181
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:14,207
A couple years ago.

182
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:16,601
How many years
have you been with this department?

183
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:19,010
What? I've been here
for three months.

184
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:20,491
Exactly.

185
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:23,961
You question me less
until you know a bit more.

186
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:26,282
- We clear?
- Crystal.

187
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:30,851
Detective Sebastian.

188
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,923
Detective, we've just
received <i>a</i> report.

189
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:36,730
<i>A witness says
there was an escape.</i>

190
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:38,370
<i>They said someone jumped...</i>

191
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:40,602
<i>...out of a window.
This is a priority...</i>

192
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:41,727
<i>investigation.</i>

193
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:43,325
We need you over there <i>ASAP.</i>

194
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:44,925
We're on our way.

195
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:47,242
Hey, let's go.
Johnson, you're the lead.

196
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:49,084
