197
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:06,171
Who's in charge?

198
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,800
There's a Detective Sebastian
here to see you, sir.

199
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:15,290
Where is he?

200
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:17,408
In the lobby, sir.

201
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,291
<i>You'll be relieved to know...</i>

202
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:24,204
...the situation is well under control.

203
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:26,601
- What happened?
- I repeat, well under control.

204
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:28,364
I repeat, what happened?

205
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:32,049
Yes, there are reports to be filed.

206
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:37,129
One of our test subjects attempted to
escape. We were forced to put it down.

207
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:39,760
- So nothing got out?
- Only a stray bullet.

208
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:42,491
- And the test subject?
- Flash-burned.

209
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:43,647
Will that be all?

210
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,487
A few things to attend to.
You could imagine.

211
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,763
Doctor, we received
an anonymous call...

212
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:51,161
...that something else
escaped through a window.

213
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:54,961
Detective, our mission at Antigen
is to develop ways of preventing...

214
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:58,761
...infection, not releasing it
into the general population.

215
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:01,880
I lost my son to this disease.

216
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:05,283
There's no room for error with me
when it comes to the safety of...

217
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:07,681
...the public.
If something had escaped...

218
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:09,888
...the authorities
would have been notified.

219
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:11,610
You are an authority, are you not?

220
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:15,163
Now, if you'll excuse me...

221
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:41,083
The guy in charge says it's nothing.
Let's go.

222
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:43,971
Yeah, and he's full of shit.
Look at this.

223
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:46,846
Want me to report it, sir?

224
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:48,530
No. I'll do it.

225
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:50,762
I don't mind. I can do it for you.

226
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:54,520
All right, sir.

227
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:21,091
The prisoner that helped me escape,
the one you called Subject 2...

228
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:23,327
...was it a hybrid?

229
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:25,681
Yes.

230
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:27,330
What were you doing with us?

231
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,326
We...

232
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,765
We help the government
identify the infected.

233
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:35,486
