238
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,530
I don't have the clearance.

239
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:48,564
You're lying.

240
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:50,891
No!

241
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:53,531
No, please!

242
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:54,488
All I know is...

243
00:19:54,640 --> 00:19:56,130
...there's a connection between you.

244
00:19:56,760 --> 00:19:57,727
Your brain waves...

245
00:19:57,880 --> 00:19:59,609
...fall into sync
when you're close...

246
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:00,602
...to each other.

247
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:01,966
You can see through
each other's eyes!

248
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:05,047
Please don't!

249
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,645
I'm the one who let you go!

250
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:08,605
Now we're even.

251
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:41,684
What the hell was that?

252
00:20:42,320 --> 00:20:43,970
Creepy is what.

253
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:45,804
- I'm calling it in.
- Let's go.

254
00:21:32,920 --> 00:21:33,569
Shit.

255
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:44,402
Don't.

256
00:21:44,560 --> 00:21:45,607
Why not?

257
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:47,445
We're the same.

258
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,245
Why are you following me?

259
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:54,050
We monitor the police frequencies.

260
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:55,687
"We"?

261
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:58,525
Do you know what attacked
that human under the bridge?

262
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:00,560
No.

263
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:05,206
Lycans.

264
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:06,521
What remains of them, yes.

265
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:11,003
They've been hiding
down here like rats...

266
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:12,047
...since the Purge.

267
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:15,329
Diseased and starving, they rarely
show themselves above ground.

268
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:18,126
Which means that something
has got them riled up.

269
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:21,250
Something you're not telling me.

270
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,208
Michael!

271
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:20,049
Do you know her?

272
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,406
No.

273
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:29,250
They will come back in numbers.

274
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:32,364
We can't leave her here.

275
00:23:37,320 --> 00:23:38,048
Come on.

276
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,120
Let's try the van.

277
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:57,969
Get in. Move! Move!

278
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,411
Three of them behind us.

279
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:26,129
Go!

280
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:30,403
Hurry, Selene!

281
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:31,686
They're getting in the back!

282
00:25:39,320 --> 00:25:41,084
Fucking piece of shit!

283
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:49,691
The girl! They're taking her!

284
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:25,005
You drive.

285
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:11,364
She's not healing.

286
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:13,841
We have a doctor that can help her
at our coven.

287
00:27:15,280 --> 00:27:15,963
How did you...

288
00:27:16,120 --> 00:27:17,281
...find me?

289
00:27:21,520 --> 00:27:23,170
Subject 2.

290
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:26,005
And you are Subject 1.

291
00:27:26,920 --> 00:27:28,888
If reed you.

292
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:33,048
Do you not know who I am?

293
00:27:34,400 --> 00:27:37,085
They told me that I had no mother...

294
00:27:37,240 --> 00:27:39,368
...that she died when I was born.

295
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:42,848
I never believed it. I...

296
00:27:43,320 --> 00:27:45,448
I felt you.

297
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:47,762
Saw images through your eyes.

298
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,846
But then someone outside my door...

299
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:55,970
...they said since I was no longer
a child, the wait was over...

300
00:27:57,600 --> 00:27:59,125
...that I'd be dead soon.

301
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:02,525
And that my own mother,
right next door...

302
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:05,606
...would never even know I'd existed.

303
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:09,562
What did they tell you of your father?

304
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:12,284
They must have told you something.

305
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:14,408
Do you see images through him?

306
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:16,046
No.

307
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:17,731
Only you.

308
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:23,327
No, please!

309
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:36,928
<i>She's never stepped foot
outside the lab.</i>

310
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:38,525
How can she possibly survive?

311
00:28:38,680 --> 00:28:41,570
I understand the risk of reporting
her escape to the authorities.

312
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:42,801
No record of her birth.

313
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:45,201
Questions will be asked.
I'm well aware of that.

314
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:47,362
But if she dies,
all our years of research--

315
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:49,090
Rather than tell me
how to do my job...

316
00:28:49,240 --> 00:28:52,130
...why not take a look
at your own professional conduct?

317
00:28:52,280 --> 00:28:54,851
And how your continual need
to endow this creature...

318
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:58,846
...with human traits has led to
the laxness of its security protocols.

319
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:01,571
It's not a human being, Lida!
It's not your child.

320
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:02,846
It's not to be coddled.

321
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:04,923
It's a blight of nature.

322
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:10,642
Stop worrying. It'll come back to us.

323
00:30:39,440 --> 00:30:41,124
Get Olivia at once.

324
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:48,291
Again you break my rules. Why?

325
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:50,488
She was attacked.

326
00:30:50,960 --> 00:30:52,007
She is not healing.

327
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:54,481
And for this
you compromise our safety?

328
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:55,368
You have...

329
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:57,568
...no reason to fear us.

330
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:02,370
Do you think I'm foolish enough
to take you at your word?

331
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:04,642
No reason...

332
00:31:04,800 --> 00:31:07,485
...to fear a Death Dealer
who fell in love with a Lycan...

333
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:09,608
...who murdered two of our elders...

334
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:12,002
...and who, at every turn,
has betrayed...

335
00:31:12,160 --> 00:31:13,400
...her own kind.

336
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:17,125
Do you know who this is?

337
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:19,849
Yes.

338
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:23,528
But it was we
who betrayed her, Father.

339
00:31:25,320 --> 00:31:26,446
Let her through.

340
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:30,171
She's not healing.

341
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:42,602
She was attacked by a lower Lycan.

342
00:31:43,440 --> 00:31:44,407
Two hours ago.

343
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:48,764
Her cell repair is...

344
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:52,130
...active but weakened.

345
00:31:54,920 --> 00:31:55,967
She has no...

346
00:31:57,040 --> 00:31:58,644
...origin bite marks...

347
00:31:59,680 --> 00:32:01,170
...or scars.

348
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:04,967
I've never seen a child like this before.

349
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:07,642
When did you last feed?

350
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:09,240
Feed?

351
00:32:10,560 --> 00:32:12,085
Give her blood.

352
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:21,202
Child...

353
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:22,691
...you must.

354
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:41,240
Slowly.

355
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,331
Slowly.

356
00:32:46,040 --> 00:32:47,007
There.

357
00:32:48,120 --> 00:32:49,724
There, now.

358
00:32:53,760 --> 00:32:55,250
She's healing.

359
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:59,002
- And quickly.
- Good.

360
00:32:59,160 --> 00:33:00,924
Take her to my room.
She needs to rest.

361
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:02,047
No.

362
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:04,606
Look at the eyes.

363
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:16,482
I never believed it.

364
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:18,405
They do exist.

365
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:22,007
This is not one of us.

366
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:24,481
No, it's something more, Father.

367
00:33:26,960 --> 00:33:28,883
What do you know of her?

368
00:33:31,360 --> 00:33:34,125
I was held captive
at a place called Antigen.

369
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:37,802
One of the other prisoners freed me.

370
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:40,124
I believed it was Michael Corvin...

371
00:33:40,280 --> 00:33:42,681
...the only hybrid I knew
existed at that time.

372
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:44,808
Yes, yes, your Lycan lover, long dead.

373
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:46,564
What is this, then?

374
00:33:48,120 --> 00:33:49,770
None of your concern.

375
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:53,125
As soon as she regains her strength,
I will leave with her.

376
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:31,041
I used to hear stories...

377
00:34:31,200 --> 00:34:32,486
...of the Death Dealers.

378
00:34:33,720 --> 00:34:37,122
That they were a thing of the past...

379
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:39,089
...never to return.

380
00:34:40,480 --> 00:34:42,209
I'm glad they were wrong.

381
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:45,564
You knew who I am...

382
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:49,562
...and yet you still brought me here.

383
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:53,370
Thank you.

384
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:55,249
You're a fighter.

385
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:58,001
We could use more like you
to teach us.

386
00:34:58,160 --> 00:34:58,888
I'm not sure...

387
00:34:59,040 --> 00:35:00,405
...your father would agree.

388
00:35:00,560 --> 00:35:04,121
There was a time when he would have.
That's why he dislikes you so much.

389
00:35:04,280 --> 00:35:08,365
I think it reminds him of the days when
he defended us with fire and steel...

390
00:35:08,520 --> 00:35:11,922
...rather than hollow words.
He knows how much we need you.

391
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:16,290
- I'm not a leader.
- But you fight for what you believe in.

392
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:18,366
You always have.

393
00:35:18,520 --> 00:35:19,362
I don't know...

394
00:35:19,520 --> 00:35:20,851
...what I believe in anymore.

395
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:23,446
I don't recognise this world.

396
00:35:23,600 --> 00:35:25,409
But you haven't changed.

397
00:35:26,040 --> 00:35:28,441
I saw it in your eyes
when you looked at the child.

398
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:31,721
You will protect her.

399
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:33,120
It's in your blood.

400
00:35:33,280 --> 00:35:34,805
It's who you are.

401
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:38,687
When you leave, take me with you.

402
00:36:40,480 --> 00:36:42,323
You distrust me.

403
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:51,643
Of course you do.
I made you feel unwelcome.

404
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:53,802
And for that, I'm sorry.

405
00:36:58,360 --> 00:37:00,044
Those eyes...

406
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:02,524
...they're special.

407
00:37:04,240 --> 00:37:07,687
I know exactly what you are.

408
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,486
<i>My father says that...</i>

409
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:23,928
...should we survive as a species,
these relics will help...

410
00:37:24,080 --> 00:37:26,526
...our descendants know
who we were and how we lived.

411
00:37:26,680 --> 00:37:28,250
And what do you say?

412
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:30,687
That if we continue to live
as we do now...

413
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:33,571
...then we disgrace the past
and don't deserve a future.

414
00:37:33,720 --> 00:37:35,961
We must resist the humans...

415
00:37:36,600 --> 00:37:38,489
...wherever and whenever possible.

416
00:37:38,640 --> 00:37:40,722
Between the first and second Purges...

417
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:45,883
...Lycan youth rallied in the same way
against the prudence of their elders.

418
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:49,442
Their calls for violent action
carried the day.

419
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:51,045
The result?

420
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:53,971
The Werewolves are nearly extinct.

421
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:57,690
Is that what you wish for us,
extinction?

422
00:37:58,280 --> 00:37:59,361
Yet you bring...

423
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:01,727
...her offspring into our home.
Do you honestly...

424
00:38:01,880 --> 00:38:04,724
...believe the humans
will allow her to remain free?

425
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:06,883
They will hunt her down
at any expense.

426
00:38:07,040 --> 00:38:09,850
- Then we can help protect them.
- Protect them?

427
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:12,130
They leave tonight.

428
00:38:12,440 --> 00:38:13,089
This isn't...

429
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:13,889
...prudence.

430
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:15,849
This is cowardice, plain and simple.

431
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,569
How dare you?

432
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:21,884
How dare you...

433
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:24,126
...do so little?

434
00:38:54,120 --> 00:38:56,407
I dreamt of the day we would meet.

435
00:38:59,160 --> 00:39:01,367
Like a silly little girl.

436
00:39:07,440 --> 00:39:10,125
You're as cold as one already dead.

437
00:39:14,480 --> 00:39:15,970
Yesterday...

438
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:18,642
...I was with your father.

439
00:39:21,520 --> 00:39:24,842
He was only a little further away
from me than you are now.

440
00:39:27,080 --> 00:39:28,730
I went to sleep.

441
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:32,562
And when I awoke the next day...

442
00:39:33,920 --> 00:39:35,729
...I learned that, overnight...

443
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:39,008
...12 years had passed.

444
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:43,644
And instead of the only man
I've ever loved...

445
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:47,321
...there stood a girl with his eyes.

446
00:39:51,720 --> 00:39:53,927
My heart is not cold.

447
00:39:54,080 --> 00:39:55,684
It's broken.

448
00:39:59,640 --> 00:40:01,290
I'm so sorry.

449
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:12,486
What is it?

450
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:15,647
They're here.

451
00:40:16,760 --> 00:40:19,047
Stay here. Wait for me.

452
00:40:19,200 --> 00:40:20,611
No, take me with you.

453
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:21,886
Please.

454
00:40:22,040 --> 00:40:25,249
I won't let anyone hurt you. I promise.

455
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:26,401
Lock the door.

456
00:40:28,320 --> 00:40:30,322
Everybody to the shelter. Now!

457
00:40:31,960 --> 00:40:33,121
No!

458
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:35,169
Prepare the armoury.

459
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:37,322
Do as I say! Go, go!

460
00:40:38,360 --> 00:40:40,601
Pay heed to me!

461
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:43,809
No! We stand and we fight.

462
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:01,401
No! Have you no sense?

463
00:41:05,480 --> 00:41:06,367
Stop this now!

464
00:41:07,720 --> 00:41:10,690
We lived safely for years
and you brought humans into this coven.

465
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:11,967
They want the girl.

466
00:41:12,120 --> 00:41:13,724
They'll stop at nothing
to get her.

467
00:41:13,880 --> 00:41:16,645
This day was bound to come,
with or without us.

468
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:19,280
Let's move!
Munitions, let's go! Everyone!

469
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:20,646
Are you mad?

470
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:23,963
We have no more than a handful
of fighters. We will be annihilated!

471
00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:26,291
And what's your plan, Father?

472
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:27,965
Let's go! Now!

473
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,966
- Where are you going?
- To get her away from here.

474
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:34,726
- He's right. I shouldn't have come.
- He doesn't understand.

475
00:41:34,880 --> 00:41:37,326
The humans will follow us out.
Hold them off till then.

476
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:39,646
They're only here for her.

477
00:41:40,760 --> 00:41:42,524
She's more powerful than any of us.

478
00:41:42,680 --> 00:41:44,284
They fear the day she discovers it.

479
00:41:45,400 --> 00:41:47,050
I have to get her out of here.

480
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:25,050
Lycan!

481
00:42:28,920 --> 00:42:30,251
Silver ammunition!

482
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:31,208
Now!

483
00:42:31,600 --> 00:42:32,522
Defend the second...

484
00:42:32,680 --> 00:42:33,329
...rotunda!

485
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:34,720
Move! Move!

486
00:43:17,200 --> 00:43:18,531
Open the door!

487
00:43:20,520 --> 00:43:21,248
Let's go.

488
00:43:44,280 --> 00:43:45,520
Move! Move!

489
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:25,486
We need to go.

490
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:51,166
What the hell was that?

491
00:44:54,560 --> 00:44:56,608
- Take her somewhere safe.
- No.

492
00:44:56,760 --> 00:44:58,171
Take her. Go.

493
00:47:33,440 --> 00:47:34,885
Where is she?

494
00:47:35,320 --> 00:47:36,765
They took her.

495
00:47:37,720 --> 00:47:39,484
They accepted her.

496
00:47:41,120 --> 00:47:43,122
As a gift from me.

497
00:48:21,240 --> 00:48:22,526
Do you know what you've done?

498
00:48:23,840 --> 00:48:25,001
Do you have any idea?

499
00:48:25,160 --> 00:48:27,322
What would you have had me do?

500
00:48:27,520 --> 00:48:31,605
Fight to the last to protect
the very one who brought this upon us?

501
00:48:32,160 --> 00:48:33,082
We're defeated.

502
00:48:34,040 --> 00:48:36,008
Our coven is destroyed.
My son...

503
00:48:36,160 --> 00:48:36,968
...is dead.

504
00:48:37,400 --> 00:48:38,970
Because of you.

505
00:48:40,000 --> 00:48:41,126
Why?

506
00:48:42,680 --> 00:48:43,920
Because he helped that...

507
00:48:44,080 --> 00:48:45,650
...child of yours.

508
00:48:45,800 --> 00:48:47,802
If they kill her, so be it.

509
00:48:47,960 --> 00:48:51,169
Your son died because
he was fighting for all of you.

510
00:48:52,760 --> 00:48:54,842
Because he knew that running
is not survival.

511
00:48:56,640 --> 00:48:58,165
Those were Lycans.

512
00:48:58,320 --> 00:49:01,290
Not extinct. More powerful than ever.

513
00:49:01,640 --> 00:49:04,450
That thing was more than twice the size
of any Lycan I've seen.

514
00:49:06,160 --> 00:49:07,002
They risked...

515
00:49:07,160 --> 00:49:11,131
...showing themselves after more than
a decade in hiding because of her.

516
00:49:11,280 --> 00:49:13,487
And you handed her over to them.

517
00:49:15,320 --> 00:49:16,287
She is the last...

518
00:49:16,440 --> 00:49:20,286
...direct descendant
of Alexander Corvinus.

519
00:49:20,880 --> 00:49:24,009
The only hybrid child
that has ever existed.

520
00:49:26,360 --> 00:49:28,681
Whatever it is the Lycans
want from her...

521
00:49:29,680 --> 00:49:31,921
...your son knew it was
worth dying for.

522
00:49:38,600 --> 00:49:39,840
What are you doing?

523
00:50:08,120 --> 00:50:09,406
David.

524
00:51:20,600 --> 00:51:22,090
A force of two dozen Lycans...

525
00:51:22,240 --> 00:51:25,289
...attacked and destroyed
one of our covens last night.

526
00:51:27,160 --> 00:51:28,400
